<div id="final" >
   <H2 class="indo">Different Indian Cuisines</H2>
  <h3 class="indo">Regional Cuisines:</h3>
   <ol>
 <li>North Indian Cuisine</li>
 <li>South-Indian Cuisine</li>
<li>East Indian Cuisine </li>
<li>West Indian Cuisine</li>
</ol>
<H3 class="indo">Explaination on the above 4 Cusines:</H3>
<b class="india">North Indian Cuisine:</b><br>
<img src="north.png" alt="width = 400">
<p>Known for its rich curries, thick sauces, and use of tandoor ovens for grilling and baking. Examples include tandoori chicken, chana masala, and dal makhani. </p>
<b  class="india">South-Indian Cuisine:</b><br>
<img src="south.png" alt="width = 400">
<p>Features coconut milk-based flavor profiles, herbs like lemongrass and curry leaves, and a variety of rice dishes like idli, dosa, and sambhar. </p>
<b class="india">East Indian Cuisine:</b><br>
<img src="east.png" alt="width = 800">
<p>Varies between Bihar, Bengal, and northeast states, with dishes like fish curry, chicken, and vegetarian options. </p>
<b class="india">West Indian Cuisine:</b><br>
<img src="west.png" alt="width = 400">
<p>Includes cuisines from regions like Gujarat, Maharashtra, and Goa, with dishes like seafood, vegetarian options, and Portuguese-influenced dishes. </p>
<h3 class="indo">Beyond the regional divisions, Indian cuisine also encompasses: </h3>
    <ol>
<li>Mughlai Cuisine</li>
<li>Punjabi Cuisine</li>
<li>Awadhi Cuisine</li>
<li>Bihari Cuisine</li>
<li>Kashmiri Cuisine</li>
<li>Indian Chinese Cuisine</li>
(and many more)
</ol>
<H3 class="indo">Explaination on the above 6 Cusines:</H3>
<b class="india">Mughlai Cuisine: </b><br>
<img src="mughali.png" alt="width = 400">
<p> A fusion style influenced by Persian, Middle Eastern, and Turkish culinary traditions. </p>
<b>Awadhi Cuisine:</b><br>
<img src="awandi.png" alt="width = 400">
<p> A refined cuisine from Lucknow, known for its slow-cooked dishes and use of spices. </p>
<b class="india">Indian Chinese Cuisine:</b><br>
<img src="indo-chinese.png" alt=" width = 400">
<p>Known for its unique fusion of Chinese and Indian flavors, using Indian spices and ingredients in traditional Chinese dishes. </p>
<b class="india">Kashmiri Cuisine:</b><br>
<img src="kashmiri.png" alt=" width = 400">
<p>Known for its rich, aromatic flavors and is deeply influenced by Persian, Central Asian, and Mughal culinary traditions</p>
<b class="india">Bihari Cuisine:</b><br>
<img src="bihari.png" alt="width = 1000 height= 1000">
<p>Known for its rich and diverse flavors, influenced by the region's geography and cultural heritage.</p>
<b class="india">Punjabi Cuisine:</b><br>
<img src="punjabi.png" alt=" width = 400">
<p>Known for its rich and flavorful dishes, often characterized by bold spices, creamy textures, and smoky tandoori preparations. </p>
